name: eyeware
tagline: lord of the rings diceware word list
body:
[Diceware](http://world.std.com/~reinhold/diceware.html) is a method of generating a secure passphrase, using random selections from a list of 7776 words.

**eyeware** is an alternative Diceware list, consisting entirely of words from Tolkien's *The Lord of the Rings*. Full details [here](https://github.com/nightsense/eyeware).

Note: the list below is for use in manual Diceware passphrase generation (i.e. actually throwing physical dice). If you plan on using computer generation instead, you'll want the [eyeware8k](https://github.com/nightsense/eyeware/blob/master/eyeware8k) version of the list...but before letting a computer choose the words, please read the last section on the [project page](https://github.com/nightsense/eyeware).
